Sentencas: Donor-substituted strontium titanates have been widely recognised as alternative anode materials to the state-of-the-art Ni/YSZ cermets in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Microstructural variations and their influence on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells based on yttrium-substituted strontium titanate ceramic anodes

Sentencas: Electrolyte-supported SOFCs based on Y0.07Sr0.895TiO3 ceramic anodes with different microstructural designs were prepared.
Titulo: Microstructural variations and their influence on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells based on yttrium-substituted strontium titanate ceramic anodes

Sentencas: Ni or Ni with Ce0.8Gd0.2O1.9 (CGO) was infiltrated onto the pore walls within the ceramic anode framework as an electrocatalyst for anode reactions.
Titulo: Microstructural variations and their influence on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells based on yttrium-substituted strontium titanate ceramic anodes

Sentencas: Performances and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy measurements of the cells were analysed in detail to observe the influence of low ionic conductivity of Y0.07Sr0.895TiO3 to cell performance, to understand how to control the degradation of the cells, and to obtain a possible mechanism for the anode processes.
Titulo: Microstructural variations and their influence on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells based on yttrium-substituted strontium titanate ceramic anodes

Sentencas: The anode design containing both functional and current collecting layers with sufficient Ni-CGO infiltration is favourable for high power output and low performance degradation.
Titulo: Microstructural variations and their influence on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells based on yttrium-substituted strontium titanate ceramic anodes
